value.name: Mammals
value.overview: The story of Jamie, a Michelin-starred chef whose world implodes when he discovers shocking secrets about his pregnant wife, Amandine. Jamie finds himself hunting for answers with the help of his brother-in-law Jeff. Through this hunt, the cracks in Jeff’s marriage to Jamie’s sister Lue also widen.

value.name: Mammals
value.overview: The series offers fascinating insights into the most successful animal group in the world. From the tiny Etruscan shrew to the giant blue whale, Mammals will reveal the secrets of their success, and how their winning design, incredible adaptability, unrivaled intelligence, and unique sociability have all contributed to their remarkable rise.

value.name: Mammals Vs. Dinos
value.original_name: 恐竜ＶＳほ乳類 １億５千万年の戦い
value.overview: Latest research has revealed that first mammals and first dinosaurs appeared on earth at about the same time and that the ancestral mammals underwent dramatic evolution while challenging the dinosaurs. It was these struggles that created the basic nature of all present mammals, including humans.

value.name: The Life of Mammals
value.overview: David Attenborough presents a nature documentary series looking at why mammals are the most successful creatures on the planet.
